Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.01,Dialogue,Credits,0,0,0,,Subtitle-source: Detective Conan - 227 [Kaizou][51177822].avi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:09.09,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs20\pos(140.8,325)}Song by Rina Aiuchi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:09.09,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs20\pos(181.6,348.2)}Koi Wa, Thrill, Shock, Suspense
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:09.32,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,koi wa thrill, shock, suspense
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.82,0:00:09.32,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Love is a thrill, shock, suspense.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.39,0:00:12.86,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,mienai chikara tayori ni
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.39,0:00:12.86,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Relying on imperceptible forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:20.70,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,kokoro no tobira tozasazu ni tsuyoku... tsuyoku...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.06,0:00:20.70,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Without locking up heart's door powerfully... powerfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never ignore the power of deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its limits rely on the wielder!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.90,0:00:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The game is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.74,0:00:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for another case's reasoning show!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.87,0:00:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.28,0:00:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:38.08,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,watashi ga kanjiteita
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:38.08,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Perhaps I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:48.99,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,toge o kimi ni no onaji you ni\Nataeteita no kamo shirenakatta
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.15,0:00:48.99,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Hurting you in a similar way that I've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.36,0:00:55.37,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,nani ni kokoro o itamete nani ni obieteita no ka
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.36,0:00:55.37,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Without realizing what was actually hurting me. What scared me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.63,0:00:59.94,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,ki ni mo tomezu motsureteku futari no shinjitsu ni
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.63,0:00:59.94,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,I was scared of our complicated truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.14,0:01:03.94,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,mukiau no ga kowakatta
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.14,0:01:03.94,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,And having to face it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.58,0:01:09.05,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,This love is thrill, shock, suspense
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.58,0:01:09.05,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,This love is thrill, shock, suspense.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.18,0:01:16.32,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,mayoi o aoi kaze ni chirasou\Ntoshite mo kakaekirezu ni ita yo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.18,0:01:16.32,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Even when I try to spread the dubieties in the blue winds...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.42,0:01:19.72,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,kono chisana mune ni wa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.42,0:01:19.72,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,This burden upon my chest is too much to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:23.30,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,kokoro no tobira tozasazu ni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.99,0:01:23.30,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Without locking the heart's door...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.53,0:01:27.80,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,tsugi e to susumu arata na fuan to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.53,0:01:27.80,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,Even if I must hold more anxiety...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.07,0:01:37.44,Top,OP JP,0,0,0,,mayoi o kakaeteshimaisou ni natte mo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.07,0:01:37.44,Dialogue,OP EN,0,0,0,,And dubiety as I go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.62,0:01:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the game center, we were taking pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.99,0:01:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until we noticed someone playing a shooting game...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.06,0:01:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Teitan High School English teacher, Jodie Saintemillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.93,0:01:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She showed Ran a game to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.83,0:02:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was quickly beat by Bitou Kengo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.94,0:02:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is until we discovered Bitou-san had been murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.71,0:02:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We gathered the suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.02,0:02:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A writer named Shimizu Takayasu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.45,0:02:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An employee of the game center, Dejima Hitoshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A taxi driver, Emori Toshitsugu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.06,0:02:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.29,0:02:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jodie-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.43,0:02:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is the one that committed the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something about that match,\NI know there's something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.88,0:02:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, what about the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't find it on anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.58,0:02:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the killer still has it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.79,0:02:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.62,0:03:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is the culprit's weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.06,0:03:09.77,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs45\pos(316,135)}The Battle Game Trap
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.06,0:03:09.77,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs45\pos(313,363)}(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.63,0:03:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Battle Game Trap, Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was picking up a 100 yen coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:17.71,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(316,366)}Emori Toshitsugu (41)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.84,0:03:17.71,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,491)}Taxi Driver
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:18.34,Top,,0,0,0,,I was buying some coffee from the\Nmachine but dropped my change.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I admit I didn't like the guy, but I respected him as a gamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.55,0:03:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous, didn't he taunt\Nyour skills at a driving game?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.76,0:03:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:38.33,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(316,360)}Shimizu Takayasu (30)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:38.33,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(315,485)}Game Journalist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.66,0:03:40.63,Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he told the other visitors: "If you wanna\Nlive, stay out of this guy's taxi."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you not have a better motive for killing him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that guy was your sister's boyfriend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:52.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister's boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.08,0:03:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister, Imoto-san, and that guy were living together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since he was your gaming partner, you\Ncouldn't say anything to him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.06,0:04:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, young man, you wanted him dead as well, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:16.64,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(326,361)}Dejima Hitoshi (22)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:16.64,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(321,486)}Store Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:17.84,Top,,0,0,0,,Half-a-year ago, this young man was\Nknown as the best gamer in Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he disappeared after losing a big match to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.67,0:04:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he decided to change his hairstyle and work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.25,0:04:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we have found traces\Nof poison in the victims blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The poison found was tetrodotoxin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it entered through the right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Tetrodotoxin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.13,0:04:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.50,0:04:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetrodotoxin, TTX for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.70,0:04:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even just half of a miligram to one miligram can prove fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If ingested, the fugu fish's poison works its way through the\Nbloodstream slowly, giving the victim a chance to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's directly injected, it means instant death. The End.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.06,0:05:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.39,0:05:22.03,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(302,487)}Teitan High School Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.39,0:05:22.03,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(305,376)}Jodie Saintemillion (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:21.90,Top,,0,0,0,,Or at least that's what a doctor friend of mine told\Nme, he said you have to be careful of it in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.97,0:05:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, that's why the weapon was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go back and look for clues at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.81,0:05:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.04,0:05:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is everyone fine with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.12,0:05:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But from where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:51.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, your left shoelace is untied.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, thanks, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should always keep it tied, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person killed Bitou-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.58,0:06:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And used the game center's environment to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.95,0:06:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did that person do it in front of the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.59,0:06:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Conan-kun? Can we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.01,0:06:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we searched the entire place\Nand found nothing like a needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.58,0:06:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The security cameras tell us that no one left during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.62,0:06:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit may still have the weapon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:07:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, we need everyone to submit themselves to a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can if you want, it makes no difference to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy died fighting me, I didn't even have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't either, I was only near Bitou-san\Nbefore the match to collect the coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.22,0:07:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you should be looking for a weapon on is\NEmori-san, who was near him during the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what about the woman playing\Nthe racing game beside Bitou-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.54,0:07:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, didn't we tell you? Jodie-sensei\Nplayed that game the entire time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.04,0:07:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, it can't be done from this game chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While sitting at this race game, you\Ncan't reach over there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that she wasn't involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.13,0:08:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I should remind you all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.10,0:08:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bitou-san was injected from the right side, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.24,0:08:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the left so it couldn't have been me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.17,0:08:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now now everyone, we're just investigating every angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, I'm rather disappointed. Especially\Nwith you, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal is smirking right in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.66,0:08:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.40,0:08:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was injected from the right side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.83,0:08:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means Emori-san couldn't have been responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.81,0:08:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Dejima-san talked with him before the battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.81,0:08:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't kill him because Shimizu-san\Nspoke with the victim just afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we were watching Jodie-sensei play\Nthe racing game, it couldn't have been her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.39,0:09:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.20,0:09:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that hated the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.61,0:09:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.84,0:09:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that hated the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu Takayasu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.95,0:09:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.62,0:09:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.26,0:09:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't everyone see me lose the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.40,0:09:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I have killed him despite that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.47,0:09:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't try that on me, I already knew you would say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:09:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.78,0:10:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, Officer Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.55,0:10:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit where they were playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This will help make everything clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.19,0:10:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please sit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? The police are taking orders from a young girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-no, Sonoko-kun is pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.14,0:10:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.55,0:10:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that guy being rough with that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.79,0:10:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't he an officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi-kun, take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.26,0:10:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.97,0:10:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K.O.!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was merciless...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.04,0:11:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.88,0:11:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Takagi-kun, I know you're competitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.52,0:11:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you were playing too hard that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.85,0:11:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko-neechan told Officer Takagi\Nto use the female character.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And told him to cover his eyes with his necktie\Nso he could do nothing during the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.66,0:11:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the one using the male character...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.40,0:11:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko told me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.47,0:11:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mind trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.28,0:11:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, it's a natural impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone expected Ran to be the female\Nand Officer Takagi as the male, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.25,0:11:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in fact, it's just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought Bitou-san chose Beika Caesar,\Nand that Shimizu-san chose Haido Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.23,0:11:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is exactly how we were fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.77,0:12:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this game doesn't display a hit-point gauge,\Nit's hard to tell who is playing as which character.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if the players' characters are\Nswitched, no one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.18,0:12:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you mean Bitou-san's was changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, after being attacked by Shimizu-san\Nand his needle, he either died or fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetrodotoxin is known to cause instant paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he didn't faint, he wouldn't\Neven have been able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait, if he were poisoned before the\Nfight, wouldn't the crowd have noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.18,0:12:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was playing the game, I didn't actually use\Nany strength and let the machine move my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.29,0:13:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The game chair's chest guard kept my body in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.10,0:13:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, Shimizu-san made this his trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:13.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the battle, you went over to Bitou-san\Nand pricked him under his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.97,0:13:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Bitou-san was feeling the\Neffects, the game was started...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.11,0:13:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A battle where the victim would be Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After doing this, you ran over to your game and picked\NBitou-san's character Beika Caesar before pressing O.K.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.19,0:13:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the crowd would think that you\Nwere the one being beat by the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't he deliver the final blow on the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he would have ended the match that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.17,0:13:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bitou-san's game screen would say "You Lose."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.91,0:13:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a tie, it would say "Draw."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that it would only say "Game Over."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.82,0:14:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.06,0:14:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a needle still have to be around here, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.36,0:14:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember them finding such a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.10,0:14:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to search you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and search me, you won't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's actually right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he doesn't have the weapon with him any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.78,0:14:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.55,0:14:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon is walking all around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.09,0:14:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dejima-san, please come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.73,0:14:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.30,0:14:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.94,0:14:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.38,0:14:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you didn't notice, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound of metal scratching the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.79,0:15:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be, your shoe has...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Shimizu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.19,0:15:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Placed the needle in a cigarette, kept it there with\Ngum, and made it stick to the gum wrapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.00,0:15:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could just place it on the floor and\Nit wouldn't matter who stepped on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did this by saying it was to pick up his lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.68,0:15:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since it was in the cigarette,\Nall he had to do was flatten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.95,0:15:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The carrier wouldn't notice it if it were flattened, and\Neven if they did, they would just throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.23,0:15:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, whether or not you removed the poison is questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you set the tobacco up beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely in the game center's restroom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.31,0:16:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you set it up in the cigarette box,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be as suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, if we can find Shimizu-san's fingerprints\Non the cigarette, we should have our evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.99,0:16:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your reasoning has impressed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.13,0:16:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this was all set up, girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That tobacco and gum are different than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.81,0:16:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, someone must be setting me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows I chew gum for\Nluck, it was even in a magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.85,0:16:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can test for my fingerprints,\Nbut you won't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.96,0:16:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! It's like that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't figure out why you used the gum to discard the\Nweapon, even after chewing gum in front of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, I discovered that you likely just took the gum\Nand cigarette from an ash tray in the game center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.28,0:17:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only reason you chewed gum was\Nin case they found the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.88,0:17:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would be a way to prevent\Nthe police from suspecting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't he leave fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.03,0:17:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he wouldn't leave any if he held\Neverything between his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, to remove the wrapped needle, all\Nhe had to do was squeeze the packaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about the coin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.45,0:17:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dejima-san, would you please open\Nthe coin box on that machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.72,0:17:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.16,0:18:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be three 100-yen coins inside now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall you removing the coins from\NBitou-san's machine earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.80,0:18:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please check the amount of coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.77,0:18:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.54,0:18:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be one coin from Bitou-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.62,0:18:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And another from when Officer Takagi played.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.02,0:18:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's another, used during the\Nkiller's trick to have an extra game.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Shimizu-san, I know that that third\N100-yen coin has your fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.67,0:18:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how will we know before testing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be, as Shimizu-san didn't\Nknow the coins were collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:19:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since he didn't have a chance to wear gloves,\Nhis fingerprints must be on that coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without gloves, he couldn't have covered his fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My fingerprints are there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.37,0:19:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I tightly gripped that 100-yen coin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.07,0:19:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As that was my "Last Game."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.31,0:19:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Last Game?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was saying goodbye to games and that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's for my sister, who's going blind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.12,0:19:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's going blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.42,0:19:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know why she's going blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's due to a lack of vitamin A.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.33,0:19:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.13,0:19:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To pay off that guy's huge amount of gambling debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She worked for an entire month and hardly ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:20:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after that guy joined a gang, she still didn't leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.61,0:20:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you wanted to play the victim in one last game?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.68,0:20:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy said if I beat him at that game,\Nhe would leave my sister alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.43,0:20:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to beat him as Haido Lucas...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:24.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just couldn't beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but now I regret doing it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because now that the Beika Caesar is gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.48,0:20:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll never have a chance to beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.29,0:20:47.32,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs20\pos(105.6,344.2)}Start in My Life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.29,0:20:47.32,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs20\pos(120,413.8)}Song by Mai Kuraki
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:54.63,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,The future will bring misfortunes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:54.63,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,ii koto bakari no mirai janai keredo
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.17,0:21:09.75,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,I will keep running to tomorrow, shining brighter than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.17,0:21:09.75,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,tashika ni ima wa ashita ni mukai dare yori mo kagayaki
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:20.46,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Now standing here, even shedding tears for the weak now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:20.46,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,koko ni tatteiru koware kake souna ima ni namidashi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.79,0:21:27.03,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Even...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.79,0:21:27.03,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,soredemo
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.03,0:21:32.60,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,We can start in my life together...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.03,0:21:32.60,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,We can start in my life issho ni
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.00,0:21:37.54,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,And stick to our dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.00,0:21:37.54,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,akiramezu yume to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:49.19,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,You can also meet the other side of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:49.19,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,nee mou hitori no jibun ni aeru kara
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:56.43,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,With one feeling, we can change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:56.43,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,kimochi hitotsu de kawarerun da
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:22:02.40,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Let us start here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:22:02.40,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,hora koko kara hajime you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.00,0:22:07.57,Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Just start in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.51,0:22:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That was impressive, Sonoko. Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.58,0:22:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were really cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were like Kate Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.42,0:22:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that American, female police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.52,0:22:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But really, you were deducing like Shinichi back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.29,0:22:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.06,0:22:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wasn't he the one that appeared at the festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He is so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.27,0:22:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not that good, he's just a reasoning otaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.90,0:22:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye Sensei, we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.07,0:22:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Jodie-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.98,0:22:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye bye, I'll see you at school tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.25,0:22:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye bye, Cool Guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.33,0:23:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right, much happened today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.94,0:23:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to admit, this place isn't so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.18,0:23:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already located one of the targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.41,0:23:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's changed his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.35,0:23:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.56,0:23:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.42,0:23:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.83,0:23:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Rotten Apple."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.36,0:23:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's use that codename, alright?
